






Exercise 2: Style the image gallery using the CSS Box Model

Create an external CSS file to style the image gallery from
 the previous HTML exercise. Use
the CSS Box Model properties such as padding, margin, 
and border to create a visually
appealing image gallery. Add padding and margin between 
images, and give the images a
border.




Exercise 3: Style a form using the CSS Box Model
create an external CSS file to style a form. Use the 
CSS Box Model properties to create a
visually appealing form. Add padding and margin to form elements, 
and give form elements
a border.